WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.439
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.439 --> 00:00:03.239
Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:03.239 --> 00:00:06.594
Well, there is a lot going on, isn't there?

00:00:06.594 --> 00:00:20.840
The whole Trump tariff thing is really shaking some things up, stirring some things up, and people ask, "Brandon," through emails and through wherever they are.

00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:23.074
It's been amazing.

00:00:23.509 --> 00:00:27.630
People are freaked out and asking, "Should we store food?

00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:29.050
Should we buy water?

00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:30.050
Should we buy guns?

00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:31.303
Should we do this?

00:00:31.303 --> 00:00:36.280
" Listen, you should not do anything by watching a video.

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:45.000
What you should do is pray and ask the Holy Spirit what you should do for your finances and for your life.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.704
I told you all I hear in part and I see in part.

00:00:51.683 --> 00:01:05.779
When the things that I see start coming up in the news, I bring the old videos out because I have so many trolls saying that I'm making stuff up, and so I'm just showing, "Hey, I do see stuff and the Lord's showing me these things.

00:01:05.779 --> 00:01:07.600
" And they say, "Are you a prophet?

00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:10.586
" I say, "No, I'm not a prophet.

00:01:10.586 --> 00:01:11.668
I'm a watchman.

00:01:11.896 --> 00:01:13.387
" I've told you all this.

00:01:13.387 --> 00:01:15.466
I'm called to pray.

00:01:15.466 --> 00:01:25.860
And I believe the Lord shows me as a watchman on the wall, looking out on a horizon seeing what's coming towards the camp.

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:29.159
"Hey, this is what I see coming.

00:01:29.159 --> 00:01:32.040
" And so far there's a lot of accuracy.

00:01:39.640 --> 00:01:39.870
Have a lot of the things I've seen not come to pass?

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:45.759
Yes, there's a lot of things that I've seen that have not come to pass yet.

00:01:45.759 --> 00:01:53.180
But the things that I've told you so far—some of those things you've seen in the news.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:56.700
So they go, "Well, what's this mean now?

00:01:56.700 --> 00:01:59.959
" Honestly, I pray none of this that I've seen comes to pass.

00:02:07.1000 --> 00:02:24.440
And you can point fingers at me, call me false all day long, and say he's making stuff up or whatever, but I'm here to tell you, we have to pray for what I've seen about China and the trade wars because it's about medical.

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:35.695
They get so irritated and so frustrated with the escalation of this that they start saying, "We're not giving you medicines and things like that.

00:02:48.319 --> 00:02:48.546
" That's what I saw.

00:02:48.546 --> 00:02:51.540
Now, is that for you to get scared about?

00:02:56.059 --> 00:02:56.469
No.

00:02:56.469 --> 00:02:58.365
It could not happen.

00:02:58.365 --> 00:03:10.270
If we pray and we ask the Father to intervene in this and pray for these trade wars to deescalate and fall apart and that they come to an agreement, then it's all over.

00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:11.110
Wouldn't it be?

00:03:18.095 --> 00:03:20.780
I mean, the ultimate goal is not for this to keep going and going and getting out of control and then we go, "Oh, no.

00:03:20.780 --> 00:03:44.502
" Everything I told you—I saw stores that were not able to get merchandise back and forth throughout all the Targets and all the Walmarts and all the Costcos and the Sam's Clubs, and that they had to take everything out of one store and put it in another store because they had to shut that store down because they couldn't get the supplies.

00:03:48.906 --> 00:03:50.706
The things I see, if you look at it in the natural, it will scare you.

00:03:56.594 --> 00:03:56.845
It will really freak you out.

00:03:56.845 --> 00:04:09.468
But if you keep your eyes on Him, if you keep your eyes vertical and you keep looking at the Father and praying over this stuff, knowing that we have authority, it shouldn't freak you out.

00:04:09.468 --> 00:04:19.289
Now, I have a lot of people all freaked out, and my job right now is I'm diffusing it to say, "Listen, the sky's not falling.

00:04:19.289 --> 00:04:20.560
" Yes, I saw this.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:23.773
Yes, what I saw about the trade wars and the things coming.

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:26.240
We should pray.

00:04:30.129 --> 00:04:30.299
That's what we're here to do.

00:04:30.299 --> 00:04:31.830
So, can we change it through prayer?

00:04:32.583 --> 00:04:32.777
I believe so.

00:04:39.080 --> 00:04:39.440
All things are possible to him who believes.

00:04:41.173 --> 00:04:44.400
I believe that every believer has the authority of the believer inside of him.

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:47.700
We have the power and authority that Jesus has given us.

00:04:54.114 --> 00:04:54.366
That as He is, so are we in this world.

00:04:57.967 --> 00:05:00.656
And if Jesus can cause peace to the storms, we can call peace to the storms.

00:05:00.656 --> 00:05:07.120
We are made in the image of God and we are joint heirs of Jesus Christ.

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:13.070
And I believe that we can do those things.

00:05:13.070 --> 00:05:16.610
Some people don't believe it, but I believe we do.

00:05:16.610 --> 00:05:19.395
So if you want to watch me, fine.

00:05:20.373 --> 00:05:25.000
If you don't want to agree with it, that's on you.

00:05:25.840 --> 00:05:30.391
I know I have all kinds of different beliefs, but I want to tell you this.

00:05:33.700 --> 00:05:34.000
People ask, "Brandon, what are you doing right now?

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.800
Are you storing up food?

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:37.467
Are you doing all this?

00:05:37.467 --> 00:05:38.533
" No, I'm not.

00:05:39.351 --> 00:05:54.800
I am not getting in fear and going out to the grocery store and buying $10,000 worth of groceries and going, "Well, I've got it all in the garage, and I've got it out here and it's going to get hot in the summer and then next thing I know it's spoiled.

00:06:01.919 --> 00:06:02.279
" I'm not doing that.

00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:10.880
The Holy Spirit didn't tell me, "Brandon, you should go out and buy a freezer full of meat at Sam's tomorrow.

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:13.720
" He may tell you to do that; He may not.

00:06:18.513 --> 00:06:18.776
But you have to just follow Him for your household.

00:06:18.776 --> 00:06:21.928
He may say to you, "Go get water.

00:06:21.928 --> 00:06:22.604
Go get this.

00:06:22.604 --> 00:06:23.280
Go get that.

00:06:23.590 --> 00:06:25.449
" I don't know where you live.

00:06:25.759 --> 00:06:30.862
I don't know if you live in a major apartment complex with 500 people around you—I have no idea, folks.

00:06:44.427 --> 00:06:44.853
If I lived in Orlando or if I lived in Tampa or a major city that I saw all those people and it's so packed full of people, I might have four or five days' worth of extra food.

00:06:44.853 --> 00:06:57.413
I live in a little bitty town with not a lot of people and a lot around us is farmers—a lot of farmers and a lot of people growing tomato plants and squash in the summer.

00:07:00.059 --> 00:07:10.533
I can go down to the local farmers market and stock up every single week and get fresh vegetables around here with apples—not oranges, but apples—and peaches and pears in the fall and toward the late summer.

00:07:10.533 --> 00:07:14.204
There's all kinds of stuff around here.

00:07:14.204 --> 00:07:16.929
So, am I freaked out about food?

00:07:16.929 --> 00:07:17.820
No.

00:07:17.820 --> 00:07:22.426
There's tons of food around here; we have farmers everywhere.

00:07:22.426 --> 00:07:27.296
Now, if I lived in Chicago, it might be a different story.

00:07:27.296 --> 00:07:28.447
I don't know.

00:07:28.447 --> 00:07:31.218
But I have to tell you, am I afraid?

00:07:31.218 --> 00:07:35.080
People said, "Should I pull my money out of my bank?

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:39.407
" I don't know what you should do.

00:07:39.407 --> 00:07:46.520
All I saw was the things I see and I relay it and I tell you what I see.

00:07:46.520 --> 00:07:49.897
Is that for you?

00:07:52.229 --> 00:07:52.560
That's for you to pray about.

00:07:52.938 --> 00:07:55.565
I do not want this stuff I see to come to pass.

00:08:06.655 --> 00:08:10.265
It's like people go, "Well, good for you, Brandon.

00:08:10.265 --> 00:08:11.639
It came to pass.

00:08:11.639 --> 00:08:14.400
" No, that means it's a prayer fail.

00:08:14.400 --> 00:08:23.120
In my opinion, if I see something that's drastic and I come on here and tell you about it and it happens, we failed.

00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:27.759
Now, I know some of the things we can stop and some of the things we can't.

00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:38.780
I know we are in the last of the last days and I told you we're going to see major things coming, but some of the things I believe we can stop.

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:45.440
And so that's my main job: to always pray and ask the Father to change it, just like Abraham.

00:08:45.440 --> 00:08:52.031
He came and He told Abraham what He was going to do and they had a conversation about it.

00:08:52.031 --> 00:09:05.640
And if you are a friend of God and you are joint heirs with Him and He comes and talks to you, He'll tell you what He's going to do before He does it.

00:09:05.640 --> 00:09:09.920
Just because we're friends—you tell your wife everything, don't you?

00:09:09.920 --> 00:09:14.714
Usually, if you have a good marriage, or your wife tells her husband everything, right?

00:09:22.549 --> 00:09:22.811
So, the Father, it's like a marriage; we talk and we're friends.

00:09:26.560 --> 00:09:26.860
And so, that's the way I look at it every day.

00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:33.520
I just go, "Hey, Lord, what's going on today?

00:09:33.520 --> 00:09:38.747
" Just like I did with New Orleans and the shooting or Trump's ear, the economy crashing afterwards.

00:09:38.747 --> 00:09:40.806
We're seeing those things.

00:09:40.806 --> 00:09:42.160
It's happening.

00:09:42.160 --> 00:09:44.480
Do I believe we have a window still?

00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:51.279
People ask, "Brandon, you said we had a window.

00:09:58.760 --> 00:09:59.029
You said we had a window of four years.

00:09:59.029 --> 00:10:00.880
Where'd that four years go, buddy?

00:10:10.194 --> 00:10:10.423
" This is what I want to say back to you: it's a four-year window of grace.

00:10:10.651 --> 00:10:23.769
I believe at the end of that four-year window—I don't know, because I'm not going to assume, add to, or take away from anything that He's saying—but a four-year window to me is a four-year window before He comes.

00:10:23.769 --> 00:10:28.777
That's what I have in my heart: that He's getting ready to come that quickly.

00:10:28.777 --> 00:10:36.631
He said it's one last call, and He's leaving the ninety-nine to go after the one.

00:10:36.631 --> 00:10:39.840
He's looking for the sinner in the way-back fields.

00:10:39.840 --> 00:10:41.580
That's what He's after right now.

00:10:41.580 --> 00:10:44.533
How long does it take to get all those in?

00:10:51.253 --> 00:10:51.564
I have no idea.

00:10:51.564 --> 00:10:57.408
People are like, 'We need to get out of here right now.

00:10:57.408 --> 00:11:01.384
' Listen, North Korea has not been evangelized yet.

00:11:01.384 --> 00:11:05.920
Has North Korea been radically taught the word of God?

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:14.211
My son told me there's 40-some million people in North Korea that have never heard—a lot of them have never heard the gospel.

00:11:14.211 --> 00:11:15.345
Is that fair?

00:11:15.345 --> 00:11:16.780
No, that's not fair.

00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:26.160
There's a lot of people in China that are still so bound because they're underneath the Iron Curtain that they have not heard yet, and Vietnam and all these other places.

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:31.652
There's a lot of people that have not had the opportunity to hear the gospel.

00:11:31.839 --> 00:11:38.109
I know that the Lord is the Lord of the harvest, and His heart is for the souls.

00:11:38.109 --> 00:11:40.222
His heart is the harvest.

00:11:40.222 --> 00:11:43.850
Regardless of what everybody wants—to go, 'Well, I'm tired.

00:11:43.850 --> 00:11:49.138
I'm ready to get out of here'—listen, I want to occupy until He comes.

00:11:49.138 --> 00:11:53.000
So, the four-year window to me is an extension of grace.

00:12:11.988 --> 00:12:12.336
Will we still see birthing pains?

00:12:12.336 --> 00:12:13.033
Yes.

00:12:13.033 --> 00:12:25.100
I'm believing—and I told you all I believe when I've prayed and I've heard the Lord—that we will have a wealth transfer laid up for the righteous.

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:28.820
If you're listening, not everybody's going to participate in this.

00:12:28.820 --> 00:12:30.320
Oh, I don't know.

00:12:30.320 --> 00:12:32.034
I pray I do.

00:12:32.034 --> 00:12:34.120
Honest to goodness, you all.

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:36.456
Am I qualified for it?

00:12:50.420 --> 00:12:50.720
I don't know.

00:12:56.731 --> 00:13:03.760
I pray and I ask Him, 'Father, make me right before You that I would be able to be used by You.

00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:17.930
That if You want to give me an idea to get wealth, then Father, to help bring forth the gospel, to do something for Your kingdom, to support people, to help them, then Father, search me and know me.

00:13:17.930 --> 00:13:46.577
' If I'm not qualified and I mess up, Father, then if it's going to cost me my salvation, if this is going to cost me my marriage, if this is going to cost me my children and we can't handle it, then by all means, Lord, remove that from me because I would rather have nothing than lose my soul to money, to mammon.

00:13:46.577 --> 00:13:53.940
But if He can trust me and He can look at me and say, 'Brandon, okay.

00:13:53.940 --> 00:14:02.535
' And He said, 'You may not be able to handle a billion dollars, son, or a million dollars.

00:14:02.535 --> 00:14:04.010
I'll give you this.

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:05.646
' I don't know.

00:14:05.646 --> 00:14:09.014
All I know is I seek Him.

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:14.400
And as I seek Him, I will find Him.

00:14:29.504 --> 00:14:30.019
The Bible says that, and all the other stuff will be added unto me as I seek Him.

00:14:31.049 --> 00:14:33.920
And if He sees that I can handle it, fine.

00:14:43.629 --> 00:14:43.779
And if He says, 'Brandon, I need you to plant a big garden this summer in the next couple of days'—I mean, He may tell me.

00:14:48.519 --> 00:14:49.459
I don't know.

00:14:49.459 --> 00:14:53.136
I'll go out there and say, 'Braden, let's go outside and get the ground till up.

00:14:53.136 --> 00:14:56.044
' I mean, that's what we'll do.

00:14:58.035 --> 00:14:58.180
I just obey Him.

00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:12.780
And He may say, 'Brandon, you need to have some cash on hand.

00:15:19.399 --> 00:15:20.280
You may need to have some ones on hand or some fives or some tens or twenties.

00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:21.542
' I don't know.

00:15:21.542 --> 00:15:24.701
Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:15:36.289 --> 00:15:36.614
I was thinking about when Mary pulled on Jesus and she was putting a mandate on that anointing on His life before it was time.

00:15:43.949 --> 00:15:44.409
And she went to Him and she said, 'Jesus, will you help the bride and bridegroom make the wine?

00:15:47.940 --> 00:15:48.215
Can you help him?

00:15:48.215 --> 00:15:52.982
' Basically, so He said, 'It's not My time yet.

00:15:52.982 --> 00:16:02.942
' But her putting a mandate on that anointing that was on His life, knowing who He was, brought it forth and He started walking in it.

00:16:02.942 --> 00:16:06.632
It's putting a demand on the anointing that brings forth the giftings.

00:16:06.632 --> 00:16:11.469
Look what happened to that feast: Jesus showed up and He showed off.

00:16:18.052 --> 00:16:18.337
And I believe as we put a demand on it: 'Father, You are our provider.

00:16:18.337 --> 00:16:19.475
You're Jehovah Jireh.

00:16:19.475 --> 00:16:27.582
' I believe that You take care of the lilies of the field and the birds of the air.

00:16:27.582 --> 00:16:32.419
How much more will You take care of me as you put a demand on it?

00:16:32.419 --> 00:16:37.720
If He took care of water and turned it into wine, how much more will He?

00:16:40.373 --> 00:16:44.925
We don't need a drink; maybe all I need is some groceries.

00:16:44.925 --> 00:16:59.759
If Mary could put a mandate on the anointing and pull, and know and believe and stretch out her voice to Him as a mother and say, 'I know You can.

00:16:59.759 --> 00:17:00.239
Will You?

00:17:00.239 --> 00:17:07.120
Thank you for doing this'—and He's like, 'Out of compassion.

00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:13.360
' If He had compassion for them, how much more will He have compassion for you?

00:17:13.360 --> 00:17:22.444
Will you just trust Him and say, 'I believe You're going to take care of me in these end times regardless of what I see on the stock market'?

00:17:22.444 --> 00:17:30.740
Regardless of what I see with tariffs, if the Lord tells you to do—remember what Mary turned to the servants and said, 'Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:17:30.740 --> 00:17:40.320
' It was an act of obedience immediately to go and bring forth as she was pulling on it and putting a mandate on it and saying, 'Help us.

00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:45.1000
' Then it was obedience to what He instructed to bring it to pass of what they were believing for.

00:17:49.216 --> 00:17:49.472
And here the wine came and God showed up and showed off.

00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:00.980
But it was obedience.

00:18:00.980 --> 00:18:08.799
So as we put a mandate on it: 'Father, You're going to take care of us.

00:18:08.799 --> 00:18:10.119
' I believe it.

00:18:10.119 --> 00:18:12.320
You've got my life.

00:18:12.320 --> 00:18:17.019
I'm not going to stress out and worry about any of this.

00:18:17.019 --> 00:18:43.383
But if He speaks to you and He says, 'All right, I know I'm going to take care of you, but I want you to go down and put the water in the jugs,' and you say, 'Well, I thought You were just going to show up and show off and do it'—well, just do it.

00:18:43.383 --> 00:18:46.620
Whatever He says to do, do it.

00:18:46.620 --> 00:18:55.450
Even if it's a can—if He says, 'Billy Joe, I want you to go down to the Walmart store and buy five cans of green beans,' okay, go do it.

00:18:59.710 --> 00:19:11.610
And then all of a sudden, you go in your cupboard and you put those green beans inside there—those five cans—and you open it up the next day and there's thirty cans.

00:19:11.610 --> 00:19:13.919
He's the God of multiplication.

00:19:13.919 --> 00:19:18.560
He will be the God of the fishes and the loaves to you.

00:19:18.560 --> 00:19:21.973
Well, I only have enough for five cans.

00:19:21.973 --> 00:19:22.924
It doesn't matter.

00:19:22.924 --> 00:19:28.940
He had enough to turn the fishes and the loaves and multiply and feed thousands.

00:19:28.940 --> 00:19:32.034
How much more can He do it for you?

00:19:32.034 --> 00:19:37.070
I refuse to get in fear over all the end-time stuff.

00:19:54.754 --> 00:19:55.062
I refuse to let the circumstances of staying horizontal, looking at things going, 'Man, what are we going to do?

00:19:55.062 --> 00:20:09.040
' and say, 'No, I take the care out of my prayer and I put my eyes on Jesus regardless of how much I have in my cupboard or my pantry or whatever I've got in my bank account.

00:20:09.040 --> 00:20:19.340
' If I've got $500 in there and I go, 'Man, all I've got is $500,' God is a God of multiplication.

00:20:26.840 --> 00:20:40.044
I told you the stories that I have that God takes a little bit of nothing and turns it into the fishes and the loaves and we're able to pay our bills for the whole month with eBay and Poshmark.

00:20:40.044 --> 00:20:45.268
We'll get down and we'll go, 'Well, what are we going to do?

00:20:45.268 --> 00:20:46.349
' Trust God.

00:20:46.349 --> 00:20:48.924
Trust God.

00:20:51.349 --> 00:20:55.240
And that's what we've done over and over and over and He always comes through.

00:20:59.760 --> 00:21:18.320
I look back at my kids' videos even tonight of what we were like ten years ago when Braden was little, and I wasted so much time worrying and fretting about how I was going to make the electric, how I was going to pay the water bill, how I was going to pay the gas, how I was going to make my car payment.

00:21:18.320 --> 00:21:37.220
I worried so much as a father that it ate me up and drove me always to be in that state of care and that state of worry every single day that it robbed me of their childhood because I wasn't able just to sit back and relax because I was always thinking, 'How am I going to take care of all these kids?

00:21:37.220 --> 00:21:39.840
How am I going to take care of this wife?

00:21:44.267 --> 00:21:44.489
I don't have an education.

00:21:44.933 --> 00:21:45.880
I don't have all this.

00:21:49.840 --> 00:21:50.240
What are You going to do for me, Lord?

00:21:50.240 --> 00:21:55.120
' Oh God, how are you going to take care of me?

00:21:55.120 --> 00:21:57.147
That was the way it was.

00:22:05.920 --> 00:22:06.120
When Megan was diagnosed and through all the things we’ve had going on, I said, 'Lord, how are you going to do this?

00:22:06.120 --> 00:22:08.133
' But God has always provided.

00:22:21.710 --> 00:22:22.020
It may not have been as much as I thought I should have, but he always took care of us.

00:22:22.020 --> 00:22:32.080
Even if it wasn't what I really wanted or I didn't get to wear what I wanted, he always took care of me.

00:22:32.080 --> 00:22:35.480
It was just a simple act of trusting.

00:22:44.869 --> 00:22:46.870
I remember the days when I told you I was excited to find shoes at Payless for the kids.

00:22:46.870 --> 00:22:56.190
You just have to be thankful and walk in the thanksgiving for what he has provided.

00:22:56.190 --> 00:23:06.960
As you walk in thanksgiving and give him glory for everything he has done, he shows up and shows off with more.

00:23:09.800 --> 00:23:10.320
I believe that's where we are.

00:23:24.311 --> 00:23:24.622
People ask, 'Where are you at, Brandon?

00:23:24.622 --> 00:23:26.488
' That’s where I’m at.

00:23:26.488 --> 00:23:33.280
I trust God, I stay vertical, and whatever he says to do, do it.

00:23:47.440 --> 00:23:47.680
Just like Mary said, 'Whatever he says to do, do it.

00:23:47.680 --> 00:23:52.249
' In closing, people said, 'I thought you saw Kim Jong-un removed.

00:23:53.493 --> 00:23:59.126
I thought you said in your last vision you saw a bomb going off on the border.

00:23:59.126 --> 00:24:01.240
' Yes, I did.

00:24:01.240 --> 00:24:09.119
Kim Jong-un was trying to be buddy-buddy with China and Russia.

00:24:11.279 --> 00:24:21.899
They were trying to bring South Korea into the pact by influencing their government and taking Taiwan back, making a stronger front for China because they're desperate.

00:24:21.899 --> 00:24:26.050
People say, 'You said you saw Kim Jong-un be removed.

00:24:26.050 --> 00:24:27.600
What happened with that?

00:24:27.600 --> 00:24:42.944
' I believe God is going to give an opportunity for the North Korean people to find him, so they don't all go to hell because they never heard the gospel.

00:24:55.190 --> 00:24:55.555
I believe God is just and he will bring justice to the injustice, and he will expose and remove Kim Jong-un one day.

00:24:55.555 --> 00:24:57.919
He will do the same with his sister.

00:24:57.919 --> 00:25:08.045
Just like he did with Pharaoh, he will lead his people out of bondage again and give them a time to hear what the Spirit of the Lord is saying.

00:25:08.045 --> 00:25:12.848
People may not agree, but I believe God is a God of mercy.

00:25:12.848 --> 00:25:18.610
We are running out of time and coming to the end of things.

00:25:37.028 --> 00:25:37.405
You ask, 'What did you think about the eclipse, Brandon?

00:25:37.405 --> 00:25:41.039
' I believe it's more than finances.

00:25:41.039 --> 00:25:45.999
I get caught up in what I say; I’m not the best speaker.

00:25:45.999 --> 00:25:57.262
I go over these videos many times in my mind beforehand because people are mean to me and I try hard to say the right things.

00:25:57.262 --> 00:25:59.695
As I said, I try with the words.

00:25:59.695 --> 00:26:04.760
Diana often says, 'You meant to say this, Brandon,' when she's sitting next to me.

00:26:04.760 --> 00:26:12.144
She doesn't want to interrupt my flow, but I’d rather she did because I say certain words while meaning something else.

00:26:12.144 --> 00:26:15.744
In my mind, it’s right, but it comes out differently.

00:26:15.744 --> 00:26:21.734
That’s when people say, 'Well, you said this,' and I realize I didn’t mean it that way.

00:26:35.410 --> 00:26:35.740
If you truly knew me, you'd know I try really hard.

00:26:35.740 --> 00:26:40.533
I'll say it again, and I hope my son helps me.

00:26:40.533 --> 00:26:43.707
I’ve told him, 'Please correct me if I mess up.

00:26:43.707 --> 00:26:47.720
' What I saw regarding the eclipse in April happened a year ago.

00:26:47.720 --> 00:26:52.046
That Tuesday, yesterday, was part of a window of opportunity for the shifting of finances.

00:26:52.046 --> 00:26:55.619
He said, 'Pay attention to Israel and Iran in the days ahead.

00:26:55.619 --> 00:26:58.639
' This is the part I left out.

00:26:58.639 --> 00:27:02.100
People say, 'You messed up on the six-month window.

00:27:02.100 --> 00:27:07.400
' I was talking about the period from November to April.

00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:09.420
That’s a six-month window.

00:27:09.420 --> 00:27:11.440
It’s at the end.

00:27:11.440 --> 00:27:13.744
The Lord said, 'I have been monitoring the hearts.

00:27:15.103 --> 00:27:17.839
I am watching to see how they drink and how they come unto me.

00:27:17.839 --> 00:27:23.240
' Regarding the river, the Lord told me, 'I'm watching the people who have lost themselves in me.

00:27:23.240 --> 00:27:35.417
' He said those who are not ashamed of how they drink or how they minister to those on the street corners—those who don't worry about being dignified or flowing a certain way, but are just lapping up the water because they want more of Jesus.

00:27:35.417 --> 00:27:38.799
From the election to where we are now, he’s looking at the heart of America.

00:27:38.799 --> 00:27:42.657
Have the people forgotten what he's already done?

00:27:42.657 --> 00:27:45.280
Have they let go of the rope?

00:27:45.280 --> 00:27:46.390
He said many have.

00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:48.560
There is a pride that has set in again.

00:27:48.560 --> 00:27:52.693
He said, 'They have had stiff necks towards me, Brandon.

00:27:52.693 --> 00:28:03.560
There will be a shaking to awaken, for America will be humbled.

00:28:03.560 --> 00:28:06.859
Through this, I will bring a great revival back to your shores.

00:28:06.859 --> 00:28:08.870
' How do you get people's attention?

00:28:08.870 --> 00:28:09.709
Through their pocketbooks.

00:28:09.709 --> 00:28:14.309
Money is America's god, along with the lust of the flesh.

00:28:14.309 --> 00:28:15.740
We have to get soul-driven.

00:28:17.013 --> 00:28:20.262
I know many of you watching are after souls and want people to come to Jesus.

00:28:20.262 --> 00:28:23.599
I'm excited you're here because that's what I'm after.

00:28:23.599 --> 00:28:26.293
People ask, 'Where's the revival, Brandon?

00:28:26.293 --> 00:28:31.151
' I don't know where the full manifestation is yet, but I know it will come out of pressure.

00:28:31.151 --> 00:28:33.080
He's given us a window.

00:28:33.080 --> 00:28:41.171
I’m believing in an 'all hands on deck' experience where people take this seriously and minister to those in Walmart or wherever they are.

00:28:41.171 --> 00:28:48.000
Not being Bible-beating, but just loving on people and showing the love of God.

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:49.679
Let’s take communion and pray together.

00:28:49.679 --> 00:28:53.164
Ask the Father what you should do for your household.

00:28:53.164 --> 00:28:58.480
Don’t act out of fear—don't just rush to buy survival food or a well.

00:28:58.480 --> 00:29:02.420
Follow the voice of the Lord.

00:29:02.420 --> 00:29:07.890
The Lord said there will be great droughts where we live and that we'll need a well.

00:29:14.329 --> 00:29:14.551
I don’t have a well yet; I priced one and it’s a lot of money.

00:29:14.551 --> 00:29:16.700
But you believe God; that’s what you do.

00:29:18.040 --> 00:29:18.347
I don’t freak out.

00:29:19.646 --> 00:29:25.257
I say, 'God, I have a need, so I sow a seed and believe for my harvest.

00:29:25.257 --> 00:29:31.669
' Lord, you’ll provide a well if you want me to have one.

00:29:32.794 --> 00:29:34.960
I say, 'Lord, this is your bill, not mine.

00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:39.866
' If you want me to have a well, you’ll provide the well.

00:29:39.866 --> 00:29:47.093
If you want me to have a house in the woods, you'll provide it.

00:29:49.279 --> 00:29:49.469
I'm not going to freak out.

00:29:50.229 --> 00:29:52.171
You can easily start asking, 'What about this or that?

00:29:52.171 --> 00:29:52.720
' No.

00:29:52.720 --> 00:29:53.504
Peace.

00:29:53.504 --> 00:29:54.288
Peace.

00:30:07.075 --> 00:30:10.069
I ain't doing all that.

00:30:10.069 --> 00:30:17.459
I'll go find a creek and get a five-gallon bucket of water and boil it if I had to.

00:30:17.459 --> 00:30:18.971
You know what I'm saying?

00:30:23.200 --> 00:30:23.640
I mean, seriously, I'm an old country boy.

00:30:35.039 --> 00:30:35.279
I just go out and find an old pond.

00:30:51.176 --> 00:30:51.554
It may be dirty looking, red water up here in Oklahoma, but you go up there and get it with those LifeStraws and drink it out of there.

00:30:54.217 --> 00:30:54.605
I mean, seriously.

00:30:54.605 --> 00:30:58.133
There's plenty of little water patches around here.

00:31:04.005 --> 00:31:04.340
You just go out there and find a LifeStraw.

00:31:15.386 --> 00:31:15.813
I don't know, and maybe do something.

00:31:20.538 --> 00:31:22.559
I probably should study it before I say all that because I have no idea.

00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:34.019
I know LifeStraw is supposed to work, right?

00:31:43.765 --> 00:31:44.080
The commercial says it did.

00:31:44.080 --> 00:31:49.660
When I saw it before, they could be lying to me, though.

00:31:49.660 --> 00:32:02.320
I'd probably go there and say, 'You go out there and drink it,' and then your brain's like, 'Raise the dead.

00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:08.595
Get up, Dad.

00:32:08.595 --> 00:32:15.486
' No, that'd be terrible.

00:32:15.486 --> 00:32:28.320
These gimmicks—there's a lot of gimmicks online, so you have to really be careful with some of this stuff.

00:32:28.320 --> 00:32:38.488
But you know, it was really cool because this one sister reached out to us and showed us these Tower Gardens.

00:32:38.488 --> 00:32:41.999
That was one of the things we're doing.

00:32:41.999 --> 00:32:46.130
That's why I have to be real with that.

00:32:49.371 --> 00:32:51.733
A Tower Garden grows vegetables all year round and it keeps them fresh.

00:32:52.100 --> 00:32:54.700
You can grow tomatoes, lettuce, cucumbers, all kinds of stuff in there.

00:32:55.390 --> 00:33:02.220
And it just grows out of a little peat pod thing, and the lights shine on it, and it grows vegetables all year round.

00:33:02.220 --> 00:33:09.040
It's a Tower Garden and it's brilliant and it produces a lot of vegetables.

00:33:09.040 --> 00:33:18.411
So if we got two of them, it produces enough for you and maybe some extra as long as you keep it going.

00:33:18.411 --> 00:33:33.497
So what I'm trying to say to you is that there are ideas, because I thought, 'Man, how do you have all this?

00:33:33.497 --> 00:33:39.059
' Who wants to eat that MRE food all the time?

00:33:39.059 --> 00:33:41.595
What about some fresh vegetables?

00:33:41.595 --> 00:33:44.710
So, I'm always trying to think about things.

00:33:44.710 --> 00:33:54.592
How do you cook some of this stuff if things were really to go that bad?

00:33:54.592 --> 00:33:59.141
Because it's nasty and it ain't healthy.

00:33:59.141 --> 00:34:01.538
Some of this stuff's not healthy.

00:34:01.538 --> 00:34:18.319
So, you start thinking about all that stuff and I just go, 'Well, you know,' so in my mind wondering about things, I think about Tower Gardens.

00:34:33.252 --> 00:34:33.679
I don't know.

00:34:35.165 --> 00:34:35.463
There's a freebie.

00:34:43.599 --> 00:34:57.991
Father, we just come before you boldly and we put all our needs—all the stuff that we see on CNN, Fox, and MSNBC, and on this channel—I don't want to freak people out.

00:35:10.770 --> 00:35:11.060
All I want to do is call them to pray.

00:35:11.060 --> 00:35:13.760
That's all I'm doing is saying, 'Pray.

00:35:13.760 --> 00:35:14.399
Pray.

00:35:14.399 --> 00:35:22.107
' My job is to call people to prayer—a call to prayer, not a call to fear.

00:35:22.107 --> 00:35:26.126
I'm never going to bring you to fear.

00:35:27.810 --> 00:35:28.429
You say, 'Well, you're scaring me.

00:35:28.429 --> 00:35:29.359
' No.

00:35:29.359 --> 00:35:32.057
I want to call you to pray, not fear.

00:35:32.057 --> 00:35:33.600
My job is: 'Fear tolerated is faith contaminated.

00:35:33.600 --> 00:35:35.040
' Being in fear is not God.

00:35:35.040 --> 00:35:36.120
Perfect love casts out all fear.

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:36.420
Period.

00:35:40.502 --> 00:35:41.988
And I believe in the power of this covenant and I believe that he'll take care of me.

00:35:44.640 --> 00:35:46.040
So, Father, I thank you, Lord, that you said you would.

00:35:49.413 --> 00:36:16.960
And regardless of where we are on this earth—there's so many in Africa, so many all around, and there's so many different beliefs on here—I believe, Father, that no matter who we are or what we believe, as long as we believe in Jesus, and that he died on the cross, and he rose again on the third day, and he's seated at the right hand of the Father, and I confessed him to be my Lord and Savior, and that you wrote my name in the Lamb's Book of Life.

00:36:26.340 --> 00:36:26.720
I was baptized in church.

00:36:37.066 --> 00:36:37.333
You'll take care of me.

00:36:37.333 --> 00:36:47.599
I believe that God has a hand on me and I take this body because you say take it often in remembrance of you, Lord.

00:36:47.599 --> 00:36:54.514
So I believe, Father, that you've got my life and you'll take care of us.

00:36:58.040 --> 00:36:58.320
And we take this body right now in the name of Jesus.

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:00.549
Lord, you were wounded and you forgive us, Father.

00:37:00.549 --> 00:37:02.920
Forgive us of our sins.

00:37:12.240 --> 00:37:12.860
You said if we confess our sins, you are faithful and just to forgive us of our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

00:37:12.860 --> 00:37:19.004
And I take this blood right now in the name of Jesus.

00:37:24.109 --> 00:37:25.178
And I lift up the cup of the covenant before you, Father.

00:37:25.178 --> 00:37:27.813
Forgive me, Father, of my sins.

00:37:27.813 --> 00:37:30.587
Wash me in your blood, Father.

00:37:30.587 --> 00:37:37.440
I've come short so many times, and every single time I don't run from you, I run to you.

00:37:37.440 --> 00:37:41.690
You know all that I need before I even need it.

00:37:44.529 --> 00:37:44.760
And Father, I thank you for the blood.

00:37:51.589 --> 00:37:51.977
And I apply the blood of Jesus over my life right now in Jesus' name.

00:37:51.977 --> 00:37:58.190
From the top of my head to the soles of my feet, I plead the blood of Jesus.

00:37:58.190 --> 00:37:59.188
Thank you, Lord.

00:37:59.188 --> 00:38:00.131
Thank you, Father.

00:38:00.131 --> 00:38:02.999
Lord, you're so good to us.

00:38:02.999 --> 00:38:09.314
Thank you, Father, for all that you've done and all that you're going to do.

00:38:09.314 --> 00:38:11.200
You're so good to us.

00:38:12.160 --> 00:38:14.920
And whatever you say to do, we do it.

00:38:21.493 --> 00:38:21.947
Just like Mary said, 'Whatever he tells you to do, do it.

00:38:21.947 --> 00:38:23.543
' We'll do it, Father.

00:38:23.543 --> 00:38:26.480
We will hear your voice and a stranger's voice we will not follow.

00:38:26.480 --> 00:38:27.280
We'll follow you, Father.

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:40.240
And we're not going to be led by our emotions or by our flesh and be all stirred up about things.

00:38:40.240 --> 00:38:49.644
We're going to be filled by you and going to be controlled by you because God, we yield ourselves to you and you're a gentleman.

00:38:49.644 --> 00:38:55.097
And Father, we take captive our thoughts and we bring them under the obedience of the word.

00:39:02.656 --> 00:39:02.880
And Father, we plead the blood over our minds today and we say, 'Peace, sisters, peace.

00:39:02.880 --> 00:39:03.200
Peace.

00:39:03.200 --> 00:39:03.680
No fear.

00:39:03.680 --> 00:39:04.834
Perfect love casteth out all fear.

00:39:04.834 --> 00:39:06.857
We're not to be in fear.

00:39:06.857 --> 00:39:09.100
We're called to pray.

00:39:09.100 --> 00:39:15.667
' Father, I thank you, Lord, for this trade war that will cease.

00:39:20.355 --> 00:39:23.288
Father, I know some of this stuff has to take place for the end times.

00:39:23.288 --> 00:39:25.227
But it will not touch our medical supplies.

00:39:25.227 --> 00:39:27.771
Xi Jinping will not touch the medical supplies.

00:39:27.771 --> 00:39:33.133
He'll have morals concerning this or our medical anesthesia or anything that comes out of China that we depend on for medical or our supplies.

00:39:33.133 --> 00:39:41.467
Father, we call a de-escalation of this trade war in the name of Jesus.

00:39:41.467 --> 00:39:44.719
And we say this will not take place.

00:39:44.719 --> 00:39:55.960
We call peace to it and that there'll be fair trade with America and fair trade with China.

00:39:55.960 --> 00:40:00.245
Fair trade all around the world, Father.

00:40:05.188 --> 00:40:05.645
And that America, we're not bullies.

00:40:05.645 --> 00:40:10.554
They will not be bullies.

00:40:10.554 --> 00:40:17.168
But Father, we set standards that we're not taking advantage of either.

00:40:17.168 --> 00:40:23.139
Father, I thank you, Lord, that there's a change of things in Jesus' name.

00:40:23.139 --> 00:40:25.250
We call a change of things in Jesus' name.

00:40:25.250 --> 00:40:30.534
Father, we pray over our economy that things will turn around.

00:40:30.534 --> 00:40:36.320
Father, that we'll not have lines down the road for no food.

00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:48.119
That, Father, that we'll not have bank runs and people lining up taking all the money out like it was in 'It's a Wonderful Life.

00:40:48.119 --> 00:40:54.091
' Father, we'll not have that kind of stuff.

00:40:54.091 --> 00:41:03.520
Father, I thank you, Lord, that people will be peaceful and levelheaded when it comes to the markets and all this stuff.

00:41:03.960 --> 00:41:12.000
I know, Father, that you told me that we're stepping into the beast system soon and this is part of it.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:21.359
So, Father, I thank you, Lord, that as believers, we are believing believers that hear you and we know exactly what you want us to do before we're supposed to do it.

00:41:21.359 --> 00:41:23.172
We're going to hear you.

00:41:23.172 --> 00:41:27.028
We're going to know ahead of time.

00:41:27.028 --> 00:41:29.079
We're not going to be worried.

00:41:29.079 --> 00:41:31.976
We're not going to be caught off guard, Father.

00:41:31.976 --> 00:41:37.017
We'll be like Abraham sitting up there and going, 'Father, what's going to happen in the future?

00:41:37.017 --> 00:41:58.475
Tell us what's coming so that we're always in the right place at the right time doing exactly what you want us to do,' and we're not Lot sitting down there in Sodom and Gomorrah going, 'I wonder,' not even having a clue what's coming in 24 hours.

00:41:58.475 --> 00:42:00.880
I do not want to be Lot.

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:06.503
Father, help me to be like Abraham that knows ahead of time what's coming.

00:42:06.503 --> 00:42:07.669
Thank you, Father.

00:42:12.360 --> 00:42:12.580
And that's what I pray.

00:42:23.520 --> 00:42:23.946
You pray that, too.

00:42:23.946 --> 00:42:31.154
Help me to be like Abraham, to be exactly where I need to be when I need to be there.

00:42:31.154 --> 00:42:48.809
Father, I plead the blood of Jesus over every single person that is represented here, over their marriage, over their children, over their households, and we plead the blood of Jesus over them in Jesus' name.

00:42:51.919 --> 00:42:52.666
Father, they have peace that passes all understanding.

00:42:59.579 --> 00:42:59.829
I thank you, Lord, that they're always in the right place at the right time.

00:43:00.079 --> 00:43:02.595
Father, I thank you, Lord, that they have a covenant with you.

00:43:02.595 --> 00:43:13.886
And Father, I thank you that you'll multiply the fishes and the loaves in their lives; no matter how much they have or how much they don't have, Father, you will provide for them.

00:43:13.886 --> 00:43:18.456
You're the God of more than enough; regardless of our circumstances, you are more than enough.

00:43:19.615 --> 00:43:25.040
And you will provide just like you do for the lilies of the field and the birds of the air.

00:43:29.919 --> 00:43:34.853
I believe, Father, that you will take care of me.

00:43:44.800 --> 00:43:45.013
I believe today, Father, that you've got my life.

00:43:47.180 --> 00:43:53.380
And we're encouraged today because we're lifting our heads up vertically and we're looking at you today and saying, "God, I know that you know what I need.

00:43:58.130 --> 00:43:58.540
You know everything that I need regardless of what is.

00:44:01.255 --> 00:44:03.040
" And if I sow a seed, you'll take care of the need.

00:44:06.186 --> 00:44:06.479
I refuse to be a hoarder; I'm a giver.

00:44:06.479 --> 00:44:16.000
And as I give, it shall be given unto me: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give unto my bosom.

00:44:18.680 --> 00:44:23.680
I believe that the wealth of the sinners is laid up for the righteous, and they may not even know why they're doing it.

00:44:25.440 --> 00:44:26.240
I have favor everywhere I go.

00:44:26.240 --> 00:44:31.200
I've got favor because goodness and mercy are following me all the days of my life.

00:44:32.290 --> 00:44:39.568
And I'm dwelling in the house of the Lord forever, and I'll not be moved by what I see or what I feel.

00:44:39.568 --> 00:44:43.488
Goodness and mercy are following me; they're chasing me down and running me over.

00:44:53.520 --> 00:44:55.187
And as goodness and mercy follow me, people are looking to do something good for me today—even if it's a free drink of something.

00:44:55.187 --> 00:44:56.120
Who knows?

00:44:56.120 --> 00:45:00.411
I'm just believing for goodness and mercy to follow me.

00:45:00.411 --> 00:45:07.152
They say, "Hey, I want to buy you lunch" or "I want to buy you a dinner.

00:45:07.152 --> 00:45:13.960
" Somebody's going to be a blessing to me today; they're going to open the door for me.

00:45:13.960 --> 00:45:15.370
Who knows?

00:45:25.440 --> 00:45:25.630
That's a blessing.

00:45:25.820 --> 00:45:31.410
I rejoice in the small things and I rejoice in the big things.

00:45:31.410 --> 00:45:37.806
God, you've got it, and you're going to take care of me.

00:45:37.806 --> 00:45:39.047
Favor is following me everywhere.

00:45:47.261 --> 00:45:47.684
I am a man of great favor; I have great favor on my life.

00:45:47.684 --> 00:45:52.640
My wife is favored of the Lord.

00:45:52.640 --> 00:45:58.860
My children are favored of the Lord above everybody else.

00:45:58.860 --> 00:46:01.480
You have to say, "I'm God's favorite child.

00:46:01.480 --> 00:46:04.400
" Just keep saying that: "I'm God's favorite child.

00:46:04.400 --> 00:46:11.760
" God is no respecter of persons, ladies and gentlemen, but I want to say it: I'm one of God's favorite children.

